<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Industry Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A ranking Chinese official has
called for people working in the arms industry to turn a new leaf
by applying the military's industry to civilian purposes.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came from Liu Huaqing, a Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee and vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission,
during a discussion with scientists and workers from the defense
industry.
</P>
<P>
Liu said China should accelerate reforms and the structural
adjustment in the defense industry, which plays an important role
in the country's economic development and national defence in
future.
</P>
<P>
More financial resources and manpower should be put into the
defense industry to fill the gap between China and developed
countries in weaponry research, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
Scientists and researchers have been called on to give scope to
their talents, enthusiasm and creativeness to develop the
country's arms industry in an effort to improve China's science
and technology and make it competitive worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was attended by more than 50 people, including
members of the Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for
National Defense and scientists and entrepreneurs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
