<HEADLINE> EC Approves Aid for Burmese Refugees in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
said today it had approved a package of humanitarian aid worth 2
million ECUs (2.4 million US dollars) for Burmese ethnic
minorities living in Thailand or recently returned to Burma after
being refugees.
</P>
<P>
The six-month aid program will finance food aid for 81,000
Karen refugees in Thailand, and provide medical aid for them. For
Mon refugees who have returned to Burma, the program will provide
medical aid covering some 10,500 people.
</P>
<P>
According to the EC, the Burmese Karen and Mon ethnic groups
have sought shelter in Thailand. Most remain refugees there, but
about 10,500 Mon people have returned to their home country in the
hope of resettling as part of a peace accord. 
</P>
</TEXT>
