<HEADLINE> Fifteen Civilians Killed in New Massacre in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Terrorists killed 15 civilians,
including 10 women and a two-year-old child, outside the Algerian
capital Algiers on Thursday night, Agence France Presse (AFP)
reported.
</P>
<P>
The massacre, which took place at 2300 (2200 GMT) at a farm in
Haouche el Hadj, was described as "butchery" by witnesses, who
provided horrifying details.
</P>
<P>
Two inhabitants of the farm were gravely wounded but managed to
escape from a team of some 20 killers armed with knives, axes and
spades.
</P>
<P>
The killings follow another massacre on Wednesday night at
another farm a couple of kilometers from Haouche el Hadj, in which
19 people had their throats cut by the terrorists.
</P>
<P>
All the victims of the massacres were buried this morning, AFP
said.
</P>
<P>
The Armed Islamic Group (AIG), the most radical of the
fundamentalist groups, has intensified terrorist attacks,
including bombing attacks in the cities and massacres in the
villages, since the beginning of the Muslim fasting month of
Ramadan on January 10.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 people have been killed in the last 14 days.
</P>
<P>
In a statement published on Tuesday, the AIG said it planned to
step up the pace of its campaign of violence.
</P>
<P>
"The war will continue and will intensify during the month of
Ramadan and we have the means and the men to punish those who are
not on our side," said the statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
