<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A 34-year old Zambian woman has
given birth to identical Siamese male twins with their heads
joining together and their bodies stretching to different
directions.
</P>
<P>
The babies, who were born in a Lusaka hospital, were lying
straight with their arms and legs moving as other babies do but
to opposite directions.
</P>
<P>
The twins were born through a very difficult operation and
they drink milk and cry as ordinary babies, a nurse said.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said the bones of the heads of the twins are fused
into each other and their brains and blood vessels are linked.
</P>
<P>
They said this was the first case as the twin babies share
brains and blood vessels, adding that they are carrying out
further studies of the case. 
