<HEADLINE> SADC Parliamentary Forum Constitution Adopted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The 12 Southern Africa
Development Community (SADC) member states ended their first
parliamentary forum meeting here today after the adoption of
the Constitution of the SADC Parliamentary Forum.
</P>
<P>
Under the constitution, the forum is committed to the promotion
of respect for law, individual rights and freedom, as well as
economic cooperation based on equality and mutual benefit among
the SADC members.
</P>
<P>
The forum is also obliged to enhance peace, democracy and
security stability in the region on the basis of collective
responsibility.
</P>
<P>
The forum will support efforts for permanent solutions of
conflicts in the region and for dialogue and cooperation among
the SADC member countries, said the constitution.
</P>
<P>
The forum also aims to facilitate the effective implementation
of SADC policies and the participation of non-governmental
groups, business and intellectural communities in SADC operations.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters of the SADC Parliamentary Forum may be set up
in Windhoek, Namibia, but the final decision on it will be made
in the next plenary assembly of the SADC Parliamentary Forum.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania's parliamental Speaker Pius Msekwas told reporters
that an executive committee, where every SADC member parliament
has a delegate, will hold a meeting in Maputo, Mozambique, in the
first week of April to pass the forum's budget. enditem

