<HEADLINE> Kostner Takes Super-G for Second Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Isolde Kostner edged
Sweden's Pernilla Wiberg by one tenth of a second to capture her
second World Cup victory in 24 hours in a women's super giant
slalom race in Cortina D'Ampezzo, Italy, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Italian skier, the defending world super-G
champion, completed the 1,650-meter race in one minute, 17.04
seconds for her fourth career victory.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's victory in the fifth super-G race of the season
added to Kostner's rare first-place tie with Swiss Heidi
Zurbriggen in Friday's downhill in this Italian resort.
</P>
<P>
Wiberg, who had won the previous super-G race at Bad
Kleinkirchheim ahead of Kostner two weeks ago, strengthened her
World Cup overall lead by finishing second in 1:17.14. She piled
up 1,189 points.
</P>
<P>
Olympic downhill champion Katja Seizinger of Germany came in
third, two tenths behind the winner, in a repeat of Friday's place.
</P>
<P>
The World Alpine Championships begin at Sestriere, northern
Italy, on February. 2.
</P>
<P>
The three-day World Cup meet in Cortina will be completed
Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
