<HEADLINE> Fritz Strobl Wins World Cup Men's Downhill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Fritz Strobl beat
compatriot Werner Franz to clinch his second World Cup victory on
Saturday to win the men's downhill race in Kitzbuehel, Austria.
</P>
<P>
Strobl clocked 51.58 seconds in the 3,312-meter race, beating
Franz by 0.57 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Strobl slashed compatriot Guenther Mader's course record
from last year of 1:54.29 by almost three seconds.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Luc Alphand, who won Friday's two-run sprint
downhill on a shortened version of the course on the Hahnenkamm
mountain, was third in 1:52.20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
