<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Leader on Meteorology's Future Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China (CPC)'s Central Committee and chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress, told a group at the
National Meteorological Bureau here today that China's meteorology
needs further development.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Qiao said he is glad to see that China's
meteorologists have had some achievements since the founding of
new China in 1949, and that "Chinese meteorologist have made major
contributions to both economic development and prevention of
natural disasters, and have made the work and lives of the general
public better."
</P>
<P>
But, he went on to say, China's meteorology must be developed
to meet the demands of the country's plans for economic growth
over the next decade.
</P>
<P>
"The scope of meteorological services should be expanded, and
the level of meteorological technology greatly improved," he
noted. He added that meteorologists should have better
working conditions, and extended greetings and best wishes to
meteorologists across the country, wishing them a happy Spring
Festival.
</P>
<P>
He was accompanied on his visit by Wen Kegang and Zou Jingmeng,
director and honorary director, respectively, of the National
Meteorological Bureau.  
</P>
