<HEADLINE> Spring Festival Reception for Taiwanese in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 25 (Xinhua) -- A reception was held in Beijing
today by the United Front Work Department of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China for Taiwanese residing here, to
celebrate Spring Festival which falls on February 7.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Tinghan, deputy head of the United Front Work Department
of the CPC Central Committee, extended greetings to the guests and
summerized China's achievements over the past year in reforms,
opening to the outside world, the modernization drive, and
diplomatic work, and called the year of 1997 an extraordinary one.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong's return and the convening of the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party are the two major events
this year. On July 1, China will resume sovereignty over Hong
Kong, undoing one hundred years of humiliation and marking China's
victory in reunifying the motherland, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said the reunification represents the aspirations of the
entire Chinese people including those of Taiwanese
compatriots. The question of Taiwan is an internal affair that has
an important bearing on China's sovereignty and reunification, he
added.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Taiwan's authorities have, he noted, stuck to
their position of splitting the country and preventing
reunification in their so-called "elastic and pragmatic
diplomacy", attempting to create "two Chinas" and "one China and
one Taiwan". Any attempt to split China is doomed to failure, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the new year, "We will adhere to the principles
of peaceful reunification and 'one country, two systems',
implementing the eight-point proposition on the promotion of
peaceful reunification of the motherland put forward by Jiang
Zemin, general secretary of the CPC Central Committee," he said.
</P>
<P>
Efforts shall also be made to promote direct exchanges across
the Taiwan Straits and to make new contribution to reunification,
he added.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the United Front Work Department of the CPC
Central Committee, Zhang thanked the Taiwanese compatriots for
their good work for socialist modernization, culture, scientific
research, and for reunification.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that they will increase their ties with
the United Front Work Department and contribute to reunification,
reforms, and opening up, as well as to socialist modernization.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference and head of the
United Front Work Department, attended the reception.  
</P>
</TEXT>
