<HEADLINE> Shanghai Builds Special Roads for Bicycle Riders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Specially built cycle paths
are to be built in downtown Shanghai to connect the Bund and
the Zhongshan Park.
</P>
<P>
The first stretch of the network, 12 to 16 meters wide, and
3.34 kilometers long, and costing 280 million yuan (34 million US
dollars), is expected to be completed within this year.
</P>
<P>
Like the Chinese capital of Beijing, Shanghai is also reputed
as a "Bicycle Kingdom". More than six million bicycles, one for
every two residents, are now used in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Roads connecting the Bund and Dingxi Road, which is in front of
Zhongshan Park, are the most congested section with road traffic
in the city.
</P>
<P>
Cyclists have to run the hazardous gauntlet of buses and cars
on crowded streets, since there are no special or separate paths
for them on the roads.
</P>
<P>
Bicycle riders can expect much safer journeys on their way to
work and back home when the network, which connects the main roads
in urban areas, is completed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
