<HEADLINE> Russia's Maslova Claims Two Golds in Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Elena Maslova claimed
another gold in the Winter Universiade when she won the ladies 7.
5km sprint in the biathlon in Muju, South Korea Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Maslova, winner of the ladies 15km biathlon, clocked 25 minutes
37.5 seconds, edging Rachel Steer of the United States, who
clocked 25:56.0.
</P>
<P>
After missing a total of three shots, she had to cover 150
meters more than the runnner up, who failed with only two
shots. But Maslova came in with a margin of 18.5sec over Steer.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal went to the Czech, Kamilla Horakova, who
clocked 26:33.5.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 500m speed skating, China's Yang Chunyuan
shrugged off a bad case of flu to take the gold coming first in
both the trials for a total time of 83.02 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Her compatriot took the silver in a time of 83.32, while South
Korea's Chun Hee-Joo won the bronze on 84.12.
</P>
<P>
In other events Saturday, Japan's Hiroake Yamakage won the
men's 500m sprint in 75.63secs, followed by South Korea's Lee
Kyou-Hyuk in 75.98, and Japan's Keiju Takahashi in 76.14. 
</P>
