<HEADLINE> HK Karaoke Fire Classified as Arson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Official sources said the
serious fire that gutted a karaoke club in Tsim Sha Tsui and
killed 15 people this morning may have been set deliberately.
</P>
<P>
The local police authority has classified the case as arson and
is carrying out detailed investigations.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen persons who either were overcome by smoke or sustained
burns in the fire are still being treated in hospitals, official
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out on the staircase of the first floor of a
building at Tsim Sha Tsui at 03:59 and spread rapidly to the
second and fourth floors which were occupied by a karaoke club.
</P>
<P>
Firemen used four jets and one hydraulic platform monitor and
mobilized eight breathing apparatus teams to put out the blaze at
05:22. A total of 42 persons who were stranded in the building
were rescued by firemen.
</P>
<P>
Of the rescued, 28 were injured and taken to hospital where
five males and 10 females were certified dead before arrival. Of
the remaining 13 injured persons, two are in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigations revealed that the blaze appeared to have
been started deliberately because it had flared up on the
staircase of the first floor of the building and spread rapidly to
the upper floors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
