<HEADLINE> Tutu's Prostate Cancer Not Spread: Doctors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Doctors have found no
evidence of cancer spread beyond South African Archibishop
Desmond Tutu's prostate gland, informed sources said today.
</P>
<P>
Further medical tests on the Chairman of Truth and
Reconciliation Commission (TRC) indicated the cancer is localized
only in the prostate itself, a TRC statement quoted Tutu's
doctors as saying.
</P>
<P>
Tutu and a panel of medical experts at Groote Schuur Hospital
in Cape Town will consider further options for treatment within
the next month, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
These options include further surgery, radio therapy or
hormone treatment, or a combination of some of these.
</P>
<P>
A 65-year-old Tutu, the former Anglican Archbishop of Cape
Town and a well-known black social activist in South Africa, was
diagnosed as having prostate cancer after a surgery on January
15.
</P>
<P>
TRC is a special organization authorized by the government
headed by President Nelson Mandela to investigate human right
violations during the apartheid era. 
</P>
