<HEADLINE> Creative Ideas to Promote Basic Law Awarded in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Making postcards carrying articles of
the Macao Basic Law, contests of knowledge of the law within family
members, promoting the image of a rabbit "Anzai" holding a book of the
law in a row were among those creative ideas awarded here today.
</P>
<P>
Other awarded ideas on the promotion of the law include drawing
lottery tickets made of bookmarks carrying articles of the law,
putting up the law posts in the street or on public buses, stage plays
on the theme of the law, and distributing picture books on the theme
to primary school students.
</P>
<P>
"Introducing the law in an interesting, easy-to-understand way is
no easy job," said Lei Peng Chu, one of the judges of the current
contest on creative ideas to promote the law. "However, some of these
ideas sound new and practical."
</P>
<P>
To be enacted from December 20, 1999 when China resumes the
exercise of sovereignty over Macao, the law will serve as a
mini-constitution for Macao, and therefore needs to be known by as
many Macao residents as possible, said Lei, who is also
editor-in-chief of the Macao Daily News.
</P>
<P>
The contest was jointly launched by the Youth Committee of the
Macao Chamber of Commerce and the Macao Telecommunications Company
(CTM) late last year. It aimed at both collection of creative ideas
and the promotion of the law among youngsters.
</P>
<P>
Eleven students' unions in Macao schools and another eleven
social youth organizations submitted a total of 22 proposals to
promote the law with a supposed budget of 200,000 Patacas (about
25,300 US dollars). One social youth organization and two students'
unions won the first prize.
</P>
<P>
"Although some of the ideas were taken use of before and some
seem similar to each other, those proposals demonstrate that the
young people have taken it as their destined duty to promote the
law," Lei said. "That is highly commendable."
</P>
<P>
Over the past three years following the promulgation of the law
in 1993, series of activities were conducted both in Macao and
China's inland to improve the awareness of the law. The promotion
campaign is expected to go further this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
