<HEADLINE> Anti-Disaster Body To Be Set Up in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 25 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government is
creating a Disaster Management and Mitigation Unit (DMMU) under
the Office of the Vice-President Godfrey Miyanda, Miyanda said
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
It is the time for Zambia to prepare adequately with
institutional capacity in anticipation of disasters as Zambia is
prone to various natural disasters which require urgent attention
whenever they occur, said Miyanda.
</P>
<P>
Under the DMMU, the government will create a data bank, train
personnel, and form an information network so as to be able to
coordinate operations facing disasters caused by water borne
diseases, floods and drought, he said.
</P>
<P>
Miyanda called on donors to offer equipment to help the
Zambian government fight the disasters, particularly drought and
floods.
</P>
<P>
