<HEADLINE> Kenya's Maize Production Drops by 17 percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Kenya harvested 24 million
bags of maize (90 kilos per bag) last year, a 17 percent drop in
comparison with 29 million bags in the previous year, according
to a Kenya Times report today.
</P>
<P>
The erratic and inadequate rainfalls last year caused a drop
in Kenya's food production, especially maize, the staple food of
Kenyan people, said the paper quoting Permanent Secretary for
Agriculture Karega Mutahi as saying on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement yesterday, Karega Mutahi said that Kenya
produced 3.1 million bags of wheat last year as against 3.4
million bags in the previous year, while bean production fell
from 4.9 million bags in 1995 to 2.4 million last year.
</P>
<P>
In the industrial sector, there was an increase in sugar
production last year, with 390,000 tons as compared to 384,171
tons in 1995 while Kenya had an upshot in the production of
coffee, tea and horticultural crop.
</P>
<P>
The statement came in the wake of a hue and cry, picturing a
grim food situation in the drought-stricken areas in Kenya's
eastern, northeastern and central provinces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
