<P>
The new schedule of power rationing will be published in the
press on January 27, the Eastern African Standard paper said
today.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative to conserve water through reduction of
hydro-power generation due to failed short rains, the company
said.
</P>
<P>
The 1996 short rainfall fell far below normal level, the
KPLC quoted the latest meteorological report as saying.
</P>
<P>
The power supply situation in the country is expected to
improve in March when a capacity of 26 megawatts will be brought
back to service and two stop-gap projects with 43 megawatts will
be commissioning.
</P>
<P>
The company expects adequate generation to meet demand by
April with the anticipated onset of the long rains beginning in
March and two units of diesel generator with a total capacity of
12 megawatts being put into operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
