<HEADLINE> Tasks for Hong Kong SAR Provisional Legislative Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 25 (Xinhua) -- The Provisional Legislative
Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
held its first meeting here today with Rita Fan Hsu Lai-Tai
elected the president of the PLC.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, seven major tasks for the PLC were
expounded by vice-chairmen of the Preparatory Committee for the
Hong Kong SAR Zhou Nan and Tung Chee Hwa.
</P>
<P>
These tasks are as follows:
</P>
<P>
-- According to the Basic Law, the provisional legislature will
be accountable for enacting laws indispensible to the normal
operation of the Hong Kong SAR, and revising and abrogating laws
if necessary;
</P>
<P>
-- To examine and approve the budget to be submitted by the
Hong Kong SAR government;
</P>
<P>
-- To approve taxation and public expenditure;
</P>
<P>
-- To debate on the policy address to be delivered by the Chief
Executive;
</P>
<P>
-- To approve the appointment of the judges of the Court of
Final Appeal and the Chief Justice of the High Court of the Hong
Kong SAR;
</P>
<P>
-- The president of PLC will participate in naming the six Hong
Kong members of the Basic Law Committee of the Hong Kong SAR under
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC);
</P>
<P>
-- To handle all the necessary matters before the establishment
of the First Legislative Council of the Hong Kong SAR in mid-1998.
</P>
<P>
Laws to be adopted by the provisional legislature before July 1
will go into effect from the day of the founding of the Hong Kong
SAR, according to a decision made by the Second Plenary Session of
the Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong SAR of the NPC held in
Beijing in March 1996.
</P>
<P>
The PLC will continue to work until the first Legislative
Council of the Hong Kong SAR is established, and the deadline is
set on June 30, 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
