<HEADLINE> Eight Killed in Helicopter Crash in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Eight People were killed when a
helicopter crashed into a mountain in Aichi Prefecture on Friday
afternoon, officials said.
</P>
<P>
The officials said the Toyota Motor Corp.-owned aircraft was
found in the mountain about one kilometer from the Goi toll
station of the Mikawa Bay Skyline in Camagorl, Aichi Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
The eight people on aboard were six Toyota employees, pilot
Hiroshi Ishihara and another crew member.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter left the company's laboratory in Susono,
Shizuoka Prefecture at 3:46 p.m. and was scheduled to arrive at a
company heliport in Toyota, Aichi Prefecture at 4:51 p.m.
</P>
<P>
It went missing after the pilot sent a radio message at 4:26
p.m., saying it would arrive at Toyota within minutes. 
</P>
