<HEADLINE> Wrap-up:  PLC's First Meeting Ends with President Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 25 (Xinhua) -- The first meeting of the
Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) ended here today with Rita Fan
Hsu Lai-tai elected as president of the PLC.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, co-chaired by vice-chairmen of the Preparatory
Committee for the Hong Kong SAR Lu Ping, Zhou Nan and Tung Chee
Hwa, started at 9:30 a.m. with the participation of the 60 PLC
members.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Nan, also director of Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch,
addressed the meeting, stressing the importance of choosing a
competent leader for the PLC in a spirit of taking into account
Hong Kong's overall interests and with a responsible attitude
towards the election.
</P>
<P>
The PLC members then adopted the method for electing the
PLC president.
</P>
<P>
At 10:15 hours, Rita Fan, former Executive and Legislative
Councillor of Hong Kong, and Andrew Wong, current president of the
Hong Kong legislative Council, became the candidates for the PLC
president through the nominations by the PLC members in accordance
with the election method.
</P>
<P>
The method for the election provides that a nominee who
receives support from at least 10 PLC members shall become a
candidate for the president and anyone who wins a simple majority
of votes will become the PLC president.
</P>
<P>
Ten minutes later, a secret balloting began and the result of
the voting showed that Rita Fan won 33 votes against Andrew Wong's
27 votes.
</P>
<P>
At 10:45 hours, Lu Ping, also director of the Hong Kong and
Macao Affairs Office of the State Council, announced that Rita Fan
was elected the president of the PLC of the Hong Kong SAR, which
aroused warm applause at the meeting hall.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970125.0124 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wrap-up:  PLC's First Meeting Ends with President Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rita Fan, aged 51, is the member of the Preparatory Committee
for the Hong Kong SAR and the Selection Committee for the First
Government of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
After being elected the PLC president, Fan said that she will
dedicate herself to Hong Kong's development and to the Hong Kong
people.
</P>
<P>
She also expressed her willingness to enhance cooperation
between the PLC and the government of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
In his closing speech at the meeting, Tung Chee Hwa, Chief
Executive of the Hong Kong SAR designate, extended his
congratulations to Rita Fan on her being elected the president of
the PLC.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that the PLC, under the leadership of
Rita Fan, will be operated effectively in accordance with the
principles of "one country, two systems" and "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong".
</P>
<P>
Despite the fact that the PLC's tenure of office is not long,
it will play an important role in shouldering heavy tasks, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that he hopes for the full cooperation between the
PLC and the just established Executive Council which was announced
by him in Hong Kong Friday and will begin to operate soon.
</P>
<P>
With the formation of the PLC and the Executive Council of the
Hong Kong SAR, and the election of the PLC president, he said, Hong
Kong's transition will proceed smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Tung said he is confident that the government of the Hong Kong
SAR and the PLC will certainly lay a sound foundation for Hong Kong's
smooth transition and its future prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
About 200 journalists from the Chinese mainland, Hong Kong and
foreign countries covered today's event. 
</P>
