<HEADLINE> Whitaker Retains WBC Welterweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Pernell Whitaker scored a
knock-out victory in the 11th round to retain his World Boxing
Council welterweight title at Atlantic City on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Whitaker threw 10 blows to knock Diobelis Hurtado through the
ropes and unconscious in the 11th round.
</P>
<P>
Before that, Whitaker was twice knocked down by Hurtado but
each time he stood up again and kept on fighting.
</P>
<P>
Hurtado was taken to a hospital after been knocked down. He
said he didn't expect the knockout and got confused about
Whitaker's stamina and energy.
</P>
<P>
The victory promoted Whitaker's record to 40-1-1 with 17
knockouts. His next opponent will be de la Hoya and the bout is
considered the biggest in the division. 
