<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 25 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.1 on
the Richter scale hit southeastern Jinghong, Yunnan Province in
southwest China, at 10:38 am today, according to the State
Seismological Network.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was located at 21.9 degrees north latitude and
101.1 degrees east longitude.
</P>
<P>
Inhabitants in Jinghong City and Menghai County of
Xishuangbanna Autonomous Prefecture of Dai Ethnic Group felt
shaking, and a number of houses in neighboring Mengla County were
damaged.
</P>
<P>
The Yunnan Provincial Seismological Bureau already has sent a
work team to the disastrous area to carry out work and make an
investigation on the damages and casualties. 
