<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) ended the week higher on strong
buying support on selective bluechips and the main board's second
liners.
</P>
<P>
Buying support on selective bluechips helped support the
100-stock Composite Index to be on the uptrend throughout the
week, which surged 19.58 points to end the week at 1,244.13.
</P>
<P>
The all main board Emas Index increased 4.26 points to 354.20
and the second board index increased 9.79 points to 622.72.
</P>
<P>
