</P>
<P>
Analysts said local retail players accounted for most of the
buying while some foreign buying, especially from Singapore, was
also seen.
</P>
<P>
They said the high volume experienced during the week, which
exceeded the 300 million mark, reflected the bullish sentiment.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the 1.5 billion ringgit (about 600 million U.S.
dollars) trade deficit for the first 11-months last year announced
Friday did not have any negative impact on the share market as the
analysts said the figure was within market expectations.
</P>
<P>
The deficit was lower by a whopping 85.1 percent 8.5 billion
ringgit (about 3.4 billion dollars) compared with that for the
first 11 months of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The analysts forecast that players would continue to focus on
selective bluechips.
</P>
<P>
The mainboard's ready turnover this week increased to 1.191
billion shares worth 6.708 billion ringgit (about 2.6832 billion
dollars) from 1.012 billion shares worth 5.742 billion ringgit
(about 2.2968 billion dollars) last week.
</P>
<P>
