United States, France, Italy, Germany, Spain, Malaysia, South
Korea, Britain, Brazil, Japan and Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The 48-meter-long bridge will see a transportation volume of
some 5,600 vehicles a day after completion. It is scheduled to be
built between 1998 and 2001, and may cost as much as 1 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
