<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belarus' Population Decreases by 0.3 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The population of Belarus was
10.282 million in 1996, 0.3 percent less than that of 1995, said
the Belarussian statistics department.
</P>
<P>
The decrease was mainly attributed to higher death rate over
the birth rate last year, reports from Minsk said.
</P>
<P>
There were 96,000 new-borns in 1996 while in the year 134,000
deaths were reported. 
