<HEADLINE> Russian, Belarussian Foreign Ministers Discuss Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny
Primakov said today that Russia is in favor of integration with
its neighbor Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Primakov made the remark at a news conference held after a
meeting with his visiting Belarussian counterpart, Ivan
Antonovich, during which they discussed issues of the two
countries' integration as well as European security.
</P>
<P>
Primakov said his government agreed on the integration concept
raised by Belarussian President Alexander Lukashenko, and the two
countries should accelerate the integration process especially in
the political and economic fields.
</P>
<P>
Primakov described his meeting with Antonovich as successful,
and said only countries with similar nature, purpose and
development prospects could enjoy such a relationship as between
Russia and Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Antonovich said to develop a healthy relationship with Russia
is the priority of Belarus' foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Russian-Belarussian integration should be
based on the interests of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
He also indicated that one of the steps leading to integration
is to establish a supra-state power authority. 
</P>
