a message to Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab Chaiyasarn, praising
the past Thai support for Australia's efforts for entry into ASEM
and hoping that the current Thai government will maintain that
policy.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers today said that Prachuab affirmed that
Thailand will continue to back Australia's bid to join ASEM, but
Australia should be patient because the issue would need consensus
of all members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN).
</P>
