It is reported that Indonesia and Malaysia are strongly opposed
to Australia's entry into ASEM, arguing it is not part of Asia.
</P>
<P>
Hogue contended that Australia see herself as part of Asia, not
just in terms of trade, but also in terms of other factors, such
as proximity, cultural relations, and ethnic mix.
</P>
<P>
Thai Foreign Ministry officials earlier said that Asian and
European senior officials had agreed that ASEM would not admit any
new members before its next gathering scheduled for 1998 in
London, stressing the issue will be considered by leaders
attending the meeting.  
