<HEADLINE> Hingis Wins Australian Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MELBOURNE, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Martina Hingis of Switzerland
became the youngest player to win a grand slam title for a century
after beating Mary Pierce of France in the Australian Open final
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, 16, showed her superb form in the first set, building
up a lead of 5-0. Mary Pierce, the first unseeded player to enter
the Australian Open final in 19 years, made a series of unforced
errors and conceded the set 6-2.
</P>
<P>
The second set was no better for Pierce, who could not find the
touch she enjoyed in the previous rounds.
</P>
<P>
Pierce made two consecutive double-faults in the eighth game of
the second set when she was 5-2 behind. Hingis took the chance to
hit two powerful ground strokes to wrap up the set and the match
6-2.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, the fourth-seeded at the season's first grand slam
event, had promoted her world ranking to number two before the
final, just behind Steffi Graf of Germany who was eliminated by
Amanda Coetzer of South Africa in the fourth round. 
</P>
