<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loan for Kathmandu Airport Improvement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 25 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) has approved a loan equivalent to 27 million US dollars for
the improvement of the international airport in Kathmandu, capital
city of Nepal, an ADB press release said today.
</P>
<P>
Besides improving airport safety and security system, the
planned improvement project in Kathmandu's Tribhuvan International
Airport will expand the international terminal and construct a new
cargo-handling facility and additional aircraft parking aprons,
the bank said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ADB bank is also going to provide a technical
assistance grant of 500,000 dollars to help transform the
Department of Civil Aviation, a governmental agency, into an
autonomous, self-supporting agency to be known as the Civil
Aviation Authority of Nepal.
</P>
<P>
According to the ADB press release, the total cost of the
airport improvement project will be 47.6 million US dollars and
additional financing is to be provided by the Nepali government
(9.5 million US dollars) and an 11 million US dollar loan from the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC).  
