<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Investment to Help Ease Ukraine's Economic Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The United States is likely to
invest 5 to 10 billion U.S. dollars in Ukraine this year to help
ease the country's economic crisis, said a senior U.S. trade
official here today.
</P>
<P>
Young Kalitsky, the U.S. trade representative to the
Commonwealth of Independent States, said that the huge
U.S. investment will also promote Ukraine's foreign trade, the
Ukrainian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with President Leonid Kuchma, Kalitsky said that
1997 will be a year of tremendous foreign investment in Ukraine,
as foreigners saw a low inflation in the country, which was only
0.9 percent last December.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. will also support Ukraine to enter the World Trade
Organization, Kalitsky added.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine, the third largest recipient of the U.S. aid, has
received about 1 billion dollars from Washington since its
independence in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Due to the unstable economic and political situations, Ukraine
received less than 2 billion dollars of foreign investment in the
past five years. 
