<HEADLINE> Rita Fan Elected PLC President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 25 (Xinhua) -- The 51-year-old Rita Fan today
became the president of the Provisional Legislative Council (PLC)
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), winning 33
votes from 60 PLC members in a secret balloting.
</P>
<P>
Rita Fan is former Executive and Legislative Councillor of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
She was elected from among two candidates including Andrew
Wong, current president of the Hong Kong Legislative Council, who
lost the election with 27 votes.
</P>
<P>
The two became the candidates for the PLC president at the
first meeting of the PLC, which opened in Shenzhen this morning.
</P>
<P>
According to an election method adopted prior to the balloting,
a nominee for the candidates for the president must be endorsed
by at least 10 members of the 60-strong PLC and the candidate who
wins a simple majority will become the PLC president. 
</P>
