<HEADLINE> Tornadoes Strike Southern United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Tornadoes lashed Alabama and
Tennessee states today, damaging homes, overturned dozens of cars
and uprooted trees, leading to one death and more injuries,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
In Tuscaloosa, Alabama, a motorist was killed when an uprooted
tree crashed his car and a half-dozen people were injured in a
tornado that also overturned 50 cars in the parking lot of a strip
mall, according to local authorities.
</P>
<P>
A section of an interstate highway outside of Tuscaloosa was
closed because power lines were knocked down onto all four lanes
of the highway.
</P>
<P>
In Tennessee, storms also damaged buildings and caused injuries
and power outages. The facade and part of the roof of a Smyrna
supermarket were ripped off, and a car dealershop was damaged in
nearby Murphreesboro.
</P>
<P>
Powerful thunderstorms together with one-inch hail hit the Deep
South today from southeastern Louisiana to the western Panhandle
of Florida, causing some injuries and damages. 
</P>
