<HEADLINE> Fewer People Die of Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 25 (Xinhua) -- Fires killed 2,225 people and
injured 3,428 last year, a drop of 2.3 percent and 9.1 percent,
respectively, from the previous year, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
There were 36,856 blazes last year, 3.5 percent fewer than
1995, causing direct economic losses totalling 1.03 billion yuan
(124 million US dollars), a 6.4 percent drop from 1995.
</P>
<P>
Assistant Public Security Minister Yang Huanning attributed the
good result to the stress of governments at different levels on
fire-prevention and increasing input in public fire-prevention
facilities.
</P>
<P>
Yang warned that the fire situation is still grave, and urged
for increasing fire prevention awareness of the entire population
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
