<HEADLINE> Brazil To Eradicate Child Labor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian government
launched a program today to eradicate child labor, planning to
dismiss some 50,000 child laborers from work this year.
</P>
<P>
The program will be applied to the regions where the issue of
child labor poses a danger for children's lives, especially in the
states of Mato Grosso do Sul, Goias, Mato Grosso, Ceara, Piaui,
and Rio Grande do Norte.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Geography and Statistics Institute estimated
that in the country half a million children aged between five and
nine are forced to work in unsalubrious conditions.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Social Assistance Ministry has created a fund to
subsidize families with children between 7 and 14 years old.
The sum varies according to commodity prices in each of the
Brazilian regions.
</P>
<P>
President Fernando Henrique Cardoso said his government would
strive to redress the injustices that still exist in the country.
</P>
