<HEADLINE> Russian Duma Adopts Budget for 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moscow, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The lower house of Russian
parliament, the State Duma, today adopted the draft federal budget
for 1997 in the fourth and final reading, local television
reported.
</P>
<P>
The draft was supported by 245 deputies of the lower chamber,
with 90 against and 17 abstentions. It will be submitted to the
Federation Council, the upper house, for further consideration.
</P>
<P>
The Russian government plans a revenue of 434.4 trillion
roubles (77.32 billion dollars) and a spending of of 529.8
trillion roubles (94.3 billion U.S. dollars), with a deficit of
95.4 trillion roubles (16.98 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The spending on national defense is fixed at 104.317 trillion
roubles (18.56 billion dollars), while that on law enforcement and
security is 46.735 trillion roubles (8.31 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The budget deficit will be covered with 49.478 trillion roubles
(8.8 billion dollars) worth of foreign loans as well as 45.9
trillion roubles (8.17 billion dollars) worth of domestic
financing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
