<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Kills 15 At Karaoke In Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 25 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 people died in a
fire that ravaged a karaoke night club in Kowloon early this
morning.
</P>
<P>
The blaze broke out at around 4 a.m. on the first floor of the
karaoke club and quickly spread to the second, third and fourth
floor. Firemen used two jets and one monitor jet to brought the
fire under control before 5:30 a.m.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that 24 casualties were sent to hospitals and 15
of them, including five men and 10 women, were certified dead
before arriving at the hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Police are investigating the cause of the fire, which is
another serious case occurred in Kowloon within two months' time.
</P>
<P>
Just two months ago, a huge fire burnt a commercial building in
Kowloon and killed 39 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
