<HEADLINE> First Meeting of Provisional Legislature of HK SAR Opens in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 25 (Xinhua) -- The first meeting of the
Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is to elect the president of the PLC by secret
balloting.
</P>
<P>
Entrusted by Qian Qichen, chairman of the Preparatory Committee
for the Hong Kong SAR, Vice-chairmen of the committee Lu Ping,
Zhou Nan and Tung Chee Hwa presided over the meeting.
</P>
<P>
A draft method for electing the PLC president will be discussed
and adopted at the beginning of the meeting, which is to be
followed by the nomination of the candidates for the president and
the voting.
</P>
<P>
According to the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR and relevant
decisions made by the committee, the president shall be
elected by and from the members of the PLC, and shall be a Chinese
citizen of not less than 40 years of age, who is a permanent Hong
Kong resident with no right of abode in any foreign country and
has ordinarily resided in Hong Kong for a continuous period of not
less than 20 years.
</P>
<P>
The 60-strong PLC was elected on December 21 last year, in
Shenzhen adjacent to Hong Kong, by the Selection Committee for the
First Government of the Hong Kong SAR. 
</P>
</TEXT>
