<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UCI to Adopt Blood Tests in Major Races </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The International Cycling Union
(UCI) announced on Friday that it will adopt blood tests in major
races this season.
</P>
<P>
After a meeting at a Geneva hotel, the UCI decided to introduce
blood tests to fight the use of EPO (erythropoietin).
</P>
<P>
Blood tests are considered an effective mean to find out who
use the performance-enhancing drug of EPO.
</P>
<P>
The UCI announced that cyclists will be tested before the start
of races and those with abnormally high EPO levels will not be
allowed to take part in the races. 
</P>
</TEXT>
