<HEADLINE> Nielsen Retains IBO Heavyweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Brian Nielsen of Denmark
retained his International Boxing Organisation (IBO) heavyweight
title with a decision at Copenhagen, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nielsen met a strong resistence from 47-year-old former world
champion Larry Holmes and failed to get a knock-out victory in 12
rounds.
</P>
<P>
Two judges scored the bout 119-116 and 115-113 for Nielsen
while the third judge marked it 116-115 for Holmes.
</P>
<P>
Holmes became the World Boxing Council heavyweight champion as
early as in 1978 and successfully defended his title 17 times in a
period of 7 years. 
</P>
