<HEADLINE> CONCACAF Soccer Head Named FIFA Vice President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Jack Warner, president of
the CONCACAF Football Federation, was named vice president of the
sport's world governing body FIFA.
</P>
<P>
Warner is to take the place left by Guillermo Canedo of Mexico
who died on Monday.
</P>
<P>
CONCACAF confirmed the move and Warner is scheduled to take the
post as CONCACAF changed its rules in 1994 to appoint
automatically its president as the FIFA vice president.
</P>
<P>
CONCACAF also voted to appoint its general secretary Chuck
Blazer to take Warner's set on the FIFA Executive Committee.
</P>
