<HEADLINE> Russian Skaters Win Ice Dance Title at Euro Figure Skating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Russian skaters of Oskana
Gritschuk and Yevgeny Platov took the title of the ice dance at
the European Figure Skating Championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian pair, Olympic champions and defending titlists,
collected half dozen of perfect scores for presentation in dancing
to take the title.
</P>
<P>
Angelika Krylova and Oleg Ovsiannikov, also from Russia,
finished second while Sophie Moniotte and Pascal Lavanchy of
France came third.
</P>
<P>
It was the second European Championships for Gritschuk and
Platov. They have won three world titles and gold medal at the
1994 Winter Olympic Games. 
</P>
