<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swiss Win Snowboard Halfpipe Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 24 (Xinhua) -- FAbien Rohrer and Anita Schwaller
of Switzerland took the titles of the men's and women's halfpipe
events at the Snowboard World Championship at San Candido, Italy,
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Rohere beat Markus Hurme of Finland in the final run for the
title. He earned 38.1 points in the final while Hurme got only
37.7. The bronze medal went to Roge Hjelmstadstuen of Norway.
</P>
<P>
In the women's event, the 21-year-old Schwaller collected 24.9
points to edge Christol Thoresen of Norway to the second place.
Thoresen scored 23.8 points in the final. Sabine Wehr-Hassler
finished third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
