<HEADLINE> Ten U.S. Children Abandoned in Squalid House </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Ten children were found
abandoned in a squalid crack house without water, electricity or
heat in Atlantic City, authorities said today.
</P>
<P>
The children, aged 1 to 16 years old, were found on Thursday
when a neighbor reported that the house were reeked of kerosene,
according to an Associated Press report. There were no signs that
an adult lived with them, it said.
</P>
<P>
The children were taken to Atlantic City Medical Center for
evaluation today. The relationships of the children were unclear
and they were said from Trenton, Camden or Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
They were bringing buckets of water in to use in a toilet. A
pair of bedspreads served as the back door in the two-story frame
structure. The 1-year-old was living in makeshift crib on a bed,
the report said, quoting authorities.
</P>
<P>
An aunt of at least one of the children lived down the street
and was checking on them from time to time, but no adults were
staying at the house, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
